etymology.description: 屮 (sprout) + 六 (phonetic component) -> original form of 夌 (líng, "climb/surpass") with 木 (tree) + 人 (person) -> surpassed/archaic form
etymology.interpretation: The character 𡴆 combines 屮 (sprout), giving it a semantic base related to growth or emergence, with 六 as a phonetic component. Historically, it was also an ideogrammic compound 木 + 人 representing climbing or surpassing, later evolving into 夌, rendering 𡴆 obsolete.
